; model-vitality.form - current floor and north star for body-readable model focus.
;
; FLOOR (2026-06-14):
;   form-stdlib/model-vitality.fk is a pure Form planning/receipt surface. It
;   names model architecture, tensor chunks, delta slices, optimizer state, eval
;   receipts, vitality receipts, and lineage as explicit rows. A focused proof
;   band verifies that a tensor chunk with a local cache carrier marked as source
;   is refused, that an eval receipt can become a body-readable vitality row,
;   and that focus is chosen from resonance, vitality, sovereignty, and trust.
;   Focused testing is part of the floor: the smallest meaningful proof should
;   run first, before broader release gates.
;   Current proof: cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk
;   form-stdlib/model-vitality.fk form-stdlib/tests/model-vitality-band.fk -> 4095,
;   fourth arm: 1 band(s) four-way.
;   Real chunk storage floor: cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk
;   form-stdlib/sha256.fk form-stdlib/cell-log-store.fk form-stdlib/model-vitality.fk
;   form-stdlib/tests/model-vitality-storage-band.fk -> 8191. This proof writes
;   a tensor chunk payload into the segmented file carrier, reopens the store,
;   reads the bytes back, verifies sha256, checks CPU/GPU/MLX/Metal projection
;   re-hash receipt rows, rejects a tampered returned payload, and routes a
;   model-vitality read through wellness/pulse/release-health signals.
;   Physical ingest/carrier floor: cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk
;   form-stdlib/sha256.fk form-stdlib/cell-log-store.fk form-stdlib/model-vitality.fk
;   form-stdlib/tests/model-vitality-physical-band.fk -> 65535. This proof
;   writes a tiny real safetensors/MLX-style carrier file, reads two tensor
;   chunks by offset/length, stores both chunks, reopens the segmented store,
;   validates chunk-set root rows, verifies CPU/GPU/Metal/MLX physical carrier
;   re-hash receipt rows, and reads a live model-vitality store row into
;   wellness/pulse/release-health routing.
;   Local physical witness: scripts/model_carrier_rehash_audit.sh compiles a
;   Swift/Metal binary and an MLX C runner. On this macOS arm64 host it returned
;   sha256 7ec1a683b7c7c46bdca8964236caed86c25acee97bb4f256e472588372d17014
;   for CPU bytes, generic GPU bytes via Metal, Metal bytes on Apple M4 Max, and
;   MLX bytes through /opt/homebrew/lib/libmlxc.dylib.
;
; NORTH STAR:
;   Model architecture, weights, deltas, optimizer state, eval receipts,
;   vitality signals, and lineage are content-addressed substrate cells.
;   Files, safetensors, GPU buffers, MLX arrays, Metal buffers, emitted
;   binaries, and download packages are cache/projection carriers only. Large
;   tensors are chunk cells with format, shape, stride, provenance, and merkle
;   roots. Mesh peers share and merge slices by content address. The body reads
;   every candidate model through the same lens tuple:
;     resonance, vitality, sovereignty, trust,
;     accuracy, confidence, energy, latency, memory, coverage,
;     freshness, mergeability, readiness.
;   That tuple tells the body where to focus next: serve-and-watch,
;   teach-trust, restore-sovereignty, seek-resonance, restore-vitality,
;   learn-more-samples, repair-mergeability, compress-or-route, or keep-learning.
;   Faster release cadence is a vitality signal when it preserves this proof
;   chain; slow unfocused gates are body pressure, not health.
;   Carrier projection rule: a CPU, GPU, MLX, or Metal buffer is faithful only
;   when its returned bytes re-hash to the source chunk digest. The source chunk
;   stays the substrate cell/store object; the carrier buffer is never truth.
;
; REVIEW TRACE:
;   The 2026-06-14 architecture review used local Grok, Gemini, and Claude CLI
;   lanes. Their shared findings were:
;     - content-addressed cells, not files, are the right source of truth;
;     - tensor chunking must be explicit before large model sharing grows;
;     - eval receipts must be durable/queryable and tied to exact model roots;
;     - optimizer state must have a named cell home;
;     - merge receipts must preserve ancestry to prevent double counting;
;     - vitality needs one body-readable door over the existing signal tissue.
;
; GAP:
;   This floor now stores real tensor chunks in the segmented file-backed cell
;   store, ingests two safetensors/MLX-style chunks by byte offset, proves CPU,
;   generic GPU, Metal, and MLX returned-byte re-hash receipts on this host, and
;   routes a live model-vitality store row through wellness/pulse signals.
;   Remaining gaps: full safetensors header parsing for arbitrary model files,
;   real MLX tensor package ingest beyond the tiny carrier witness, production
;   wellness/pulse ingestion from deployed live model-vitality rows, and large
;   multi-segment model sharing by merkle across mesh peers.

(model-vitality-surface
  (floor
    (rows
      model-architecture
      tensor-chunk
      delta-slice
      optimizer-state
      eval-receipt
      vitality-receipt
      lineage)
    (proved-by "form/form-stdlib/tests/model-vitality-band.fk")
    (verdict 4095)
    (fourth-arm four-way)
    (real-storage-proof "form/form-stdlib/tests/model-vitality-storage-band.fk -> 8191")
    (physical-carrier-proof "form/form-stdlib/tests/model-vitality-physical-band.fk -> 65535")
    (native-carrier-witness "scripts/model_carrier_rehash_audit.sh")
    (release-health smallest-focused-proof-first))
  (north-star
    (source-of-truth substrate-cells)
    (carrier-cache-only files gpu-buffers mlx-arrays metal-buffers emitted-binaries)
    (focus-lenses resonance vitality sovereignty trust)
    (share-by merkle-root)
    (read-by body-vitality-door)
    (rehash-rule carrier-returned-bytes-match-source-chunk-digest)
    (physical-carriers cpu-buffer gpu-buffer metal-buffer mlx-array)
    (ingest-carriers safetensors mlx-package)
    (wellness-pulse-routing model-vitality-row-chooses-focus)
    (release-vitality fast-proofed-release-cadence)))
